Business Brief -- Rogers Communications Inc.:
   Firm Plans Public Offering
   For Part of Its Phone Unit
In trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange yesterday, Rogers
Cantel shares closed at C$28.50, off 25 Canadian cents.
   Proceeds from the sale will be used to help pay down
Rogers Communications's bank debt of about C$800 million, the
company said.
   Rogers said that it will retain an 80% equity interest in
the Cantel unit after the issue and will keep voting control
through its ownership of all the unit's Class A multiple
voting shares.